# Fintech Product Architecture

## Balance Display
- Always show: currency symbol, thousands separators, two decimal
  places. Example: $1,245.34
- Use skeleton loaders when balance data is loading.

## Transaction History
- Always display: transaction name, date, amount, debit/credit
  indicator.
- Green = money received. Red = money spent.
- Support pagination or infinite scroll. Never load unlimited lists.

## Transfers and Payments
- All transfer flows: Enter amount → Select recipient →
  Review details → Confirm.
- Confirmation screen must show: amount, recipient, account used,
  estimated processing time.
- Users must explicitly confirm before any transfer executes.

## Financial Actions
- Dangerous actions require confirmation dialogs:
  sending money, deleting payment methods, closing accounts.

## Error Handling
- Bad: "Error processing request"
- Good: "We couldn't send your payment. Please check your
  balance or try again."

## Sensitive Data
- Card numbers: show last four digits only. Example: **** 4821
- SSN must never appear in the UI after collection.

## Loading States
- All financial actions must show a loading state.
- Disable buttons during submission to prevent duplicate actions.

## Data Accuracy
- Financial data must always come from the server.
- Never calculate balances on the client.
